  "prompt": "How many layers should you wear on cold winter days?",
  "response": "On cold winter days, it's recommended to wear 3-4 layers for optimal warmth and comfort:\n\n1. Base layer (closest to skin)\n- Moisture-wicking material like thermal underwear\n- Helps keep skin dry and regulates body temperature\n\n2. Middle layer(s)\n- Insulating materials like fleece or wool\n- Traps warm air and provides additional warmth\n- Can use 1-2 middle layers depending on temperature\n\n3. Outer layer\n- Windproof and waterproof jacket\n- Protects against wind, snow, and rain\n- Should be breathable to prevent overheating\n\nOptional: Extra insulating layer if extremely cold\n\nThe key is to dress in layers that you can add or remove as needed to regulate body temperature.",
